etown university in washington dc where their son sean  has completed his sophomore year asked if he pressured his son to attend his alma mater todman said with a laugh what i learned is if you pressure them then theyre definitely not going instead he told his son i had a great time there i thought it was a good schoolthe todmans daughter melanie  graduated this spring from carleton college in northfield minn with a major in political science and minor in lawtodman was running wang laboratories business in the uk when he joined whirlpool as director finance united kingdom the computer hardware and software company is no longer in businesstodman said he had some hesitancy about changing employers because i initially thought ôthis is appliances and i was in the computer industry at a time when it was fast movingalthough the appliance industry might have seemed less glamorous he said i joined because i thought ôgreat company great peopleand i thought i would have lots of opportunity to growtodman went from his whirlpool job in the uk to general manager northern europe and then vice president consumer services whirlpool europehe was promoted to and finally moved to corporate headquarters in the twin cities in  as controller north america in  he was promoted to vice president product management in  to vice president sears sales and marketing and in  to senior vice president sales and marketing north americain march  he became executive vice president north america but in october of that year he went back to europe as executive vice president and president whirlpool europewhile todman and his wife were in italy their children attended and graduated from their alma mater northfield mount hermon as president of whirlpool international he said probably  to  percent of his time is spent being someplace else i have a belief i have a view ð i guess a philosophy ð that says that the only way i can do this job is by knowing and understanding the markets and the regions that were doing business in so i have to be therein midjune he returned from about five weeks visiting brazil india china italy france and the uk it was wonderful todman said of his trip i had a great time one of the things the pleasures is the diversity and the variety that you see between countries …you also see all the opportunities because you get ideas when you do that todman said whirlpools worldwide operations enable it to quickly share products developed in one region with another for instance the technology for whirlpools frontloading energysaving duet clothes washer was developed in germanya barrier to growth in appliance sales in many lessdeveloped countries has been creation of a reliable electricity supplywithout it for instance people must shop daily for groceries since they dont have refrigerators but with more countries developing reliable electrical systems that provides us a huge opportunity todman saidhe said whirlpools international business now totals about  billion a year by  he said he expects it to reach  billioneven when todman is in his office at whirlpool corporate headquarters the hours can be extremely long because of the time differences for instance asia is  or  hours ahead of benton harbor he said he sometimes works from  am to  or  at nightwhen hes not working todman said i like to read i like to be outside i like to play tennis … and im getting ready to take up golfand at the time of the heraldpalladium interview he was looking forward to a weekend fishing trip with his son discuss print posted in localnews on wednesday july    am rules of conduct  keep it clean please avoid obscene vulgar lewd racist or sexuallyoriented language  dont threaten or abuse threats of harming another person will not be tolerated and please turn off caps lock  be truthful dont knowingly lie about anyone or anything  be nice no racism sexism or any sort of ism that is degrading to another person  be proactive use the report link on each comment to let us know of ab